Title : Cornice Peak (Selkirk Mountains)
Text : '''Cornice Peak''',  2824 m -> 9265 feet,<ref>[http://bivouac.com/MtnPg.asp?MtnId=2302 Bivouac Mountain Encyclopedia entry]</ref> is a [[mountain]] in the [[Sir Sandford Range]] of the [[Selkirk Mountains]] subdivision of the [[Columbia Mountains]] in [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]].  It is just southwest of Gold Arm of Columbia Reach of [[Kinbasket Lake]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/13066.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Cornice Peak"]</ref>

